<exercise>
  <title>V10 - Basis of Solution Space (ver. 926)</title>
  <statement>
    <p>Find a basis for the solution space of the homogeneous system <md><mrow> -5 x_ 1 + 5 x_ 2 -5 x_ 3 &amp;= 0  </mrow> <mrow> &amp;= 0  </mrow> <mrow> 1 x_ 1 -9 x_ 2 + 5 x_ 3 -4 x_ 4 &amp;= 0  </mrow> <mrow> 1 x_ 1 + 1 x_ 2 + 1 x_ 4 &amp;= 0  </mrow> </md></p> 
  </statement>

  <answer>
  <p> A basis is   <me>\left\{\left[\begin{array}{c}
-\frac{1}{2} \\
\frac{1}{2} \\
1 \\
0
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-\frac{1}{2} \\
-\frac{1}{2} \\
0 \\
1
\end{array}\right]\right\}.</me>
  </p>
  </answer>
</exercise>
